@page
@{
    Layout = null;
}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>JO 2024 Paris</title>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link href="~/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css">
    <link href="~/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <!-- ======= Header ======= -->
    <header id="header" class="d-flex align-items-center ">
        <div class="container d-flex flex-column align-items-center">
            <div>
                <a href="/"><img class="d-block w-100" src="~/img/banner2004.jpg" alt="Ticketing-info"></a>
            </div>

            <h1 class="mt-3">Ticketing information</h1>
            <h2>Paris 2024 Olympic Games - July 26 to August 11, 2024</h2>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
                <h1 style="color:#24b7a4">
                    <a href="/"><i class="bi bi-house-up-fill"></i></i></a>
                    <a onclick="window.history.back()"><i class="bi bi-arrow-left-circle-fill"></i></a>
                </h1>
            </div>
            <div class="justify-content-center">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="title"><i class="bi bi-yin-yang"></i> What is the Solo offer ?</h3>
                    <h4>
                        <p>The Solo Pass allows you to discover several sports on the same day, among 3 to 7 sports sessions, at the single price of €24.</p>
                        <p>
                            Two types of passes are offered.
                            The Paris Center Discovery Pass allows you to plan your day by choosing, depending on the selected day (from August 29 to September 7, 2024), among 3 to 7 sessions, the following Para sports:
                            - Armchair Fencing (Grand Palais)
                            - Para Taekwondo (Grand Palais)
                            - Para Judo (Arena Champ-de-Mars)
                            - Wheelchair rugby (Arena Champ-de-Mars)
                            - Blind football (Eiffel Tower Stadium)
                            - Para Archery (Disabled)
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The Paris Sud Discovery Pass allows you to plan your day by choosing, depending on the selected day (from August 29 to September 7, 2024), among 6 to 7 sessions, the following Para sports:
                            - Boccia (Arena Paris Sud 1)
                            - Para table tennis (Arena Paris Sud 4)
                            - Goalball (Arena Paris Sud 6)
                        </p>
                    </h4>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="title"><i class="bi bi-yin-yang"></i> What is the Duo offer ?</h3>
                    <h4>
                        <p>The Duo Pass allows you to discover several sports on the same day, among 3 to 7 sports sessions, at the single price of €50.</p>
                        <p>
                            Two types of passes are offered.
                            The Paris Center Discovery Pass allows you to plan your day by choosing, depending on the selected day (from August 29 to September 7, 2024), among 3 to 7 sessions, the following Para sports:
                            - Armchair Fencing (Grand Palais)
                            - Para Taekwondo (Grand Palais)
                            - Para Judo (Arena Champ-de-Mars)
                            - Wheelchair rugby (Arena Champ-de-Mars)
                            - Blind football (Eiffel Tower Stadium)
                            - Para Archery (Disabled)
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            The Paris Sud Discovery Pass allows you to plan your day by choosing, depending on the selected day (from August 29 to September 7, 2024), among 6 to 7 sessions, the following Para sports:
                            - Boccia (Arena Paris Sud 1)
                            - Para table tennis (Arena Paris Sud 4)
                            - Goalball (Arena Paris Sud 6)
                        </p>
                    </h4>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="title"><i class="bi bi-yin-yang"></i> What is the Family offer ?</h3>
                    <h4>
                        <p>Experience the emotions of the Paralympic Games and discover Para sports as a family while benefiting from an advantageous rate for your children.</p>
                        <p>
                            With the Family offer, for 2 “standard – Family Offer” tickets purchased, you can buy up to 2 children’s tickets for €10!
                            This limited offer is available on all sports sessions (excluding opening and closing ceremonies). The Family offer cannot be combined with the Discovery Pass.
                        </p>
                        <p>People wishing one or more PSH/PFR places as part of a Family offer must contact Customer Service via our contact form. You will be asked for proof for any purchase of PFR or PSH tickets (details to come).</p>
                    </h4>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="title"><i class="bi bi-yin-yang"></i> What is the Group offer ?</h3>
                    <h4>
                        <p>Paris 2024 allows you to purchase more than 10 tickets for certain sessions of the Olympic and Paralympic Games. If you are a group/CSE, you can then claim this group offer. Here are the various details of the offer:</p>
                        <p><strong>Sports available for Group / CSE ticketing:</strong></p>
                        <p><u>Olympic Games</u>: Regional men's and women's football tournaments</p>
                        <p><u>Paralympic Games</u>: Wheelchair basketball / Blind football / Para athletics / Para rowing / Para Badminton / Para canoeing / Para weightlifting / Para Judo / Para swimming / Wheelchair rugby / Wheelchair tennis</p>
                    </h4>
                </div>
                
            </div>
        </div>
    </header><!-- End #header -->
    <partial name="_FooterLayoutNull" />
</body>
</html>
